name: Christian Cuevas
tagline: Everything you need to know about Christian Cuevas
body:
Hello, 

I am Christian Cuevas. I am leaving my resume here for now, but I will try to make this more interesting as time goes on.

**Work Experience**

    **Facebook, Inc.**						June 2015 to August 2015
    Facebook University Intern
    Worked with two other interns under the mentorship of a Facebook software developer to create an Android app. 

    **Department of Computer Science, UW-Madison**	            January 2014 to Present
    Team Leader, Wisconsin Emerging Scholars - Computer Science
    Lead CS 302: Introduction to Programming discussion section of 8-10 students. 

    **Wisconsin Center for Education Research (Wei LAB), UW-Madison**	   July 2014 to May 2015
    Mobile Application Programmer
    Design user interface and implement the Wisconsin Equity and Inclusion Laboratory app for iOS and Android, 
    including data collection and analytics.        
    Develop and oversee technology projects for the Wisconsin Equity and Inclusion Lab.     

    **Department of Computer Science, UW-Madison**	           June 2014 to August 2014
    Student Staff at SOAR (Freshman Orientation)
    Advise incoming Freshman on options & benefits of studying Computer Science at UW. 

***


**Education**

    Currently Enrolled (First Year) - University of Wisconsin-Madison Pursuing B.S. Computer Science            
    4.0 GPA - UW Courses Through Spring 2014 Completed While Attending High School (29 Total Credits)        
    2012   Math 234: Multivariable Calculus (A) -- Physics 207: General Physics (A)
    2013   CS 302: Introduction to Programming (A) 
    Math 340: Elementary Matrix & Linear Algebra (A)
    CS 304: Wisconsin Emerging Scholars - Computer Science (A)
    CS 298: Directed Study in Computer Science (Not Graded)
    CS 367: Introduction to Data Structures (A)
    Math 240: Introduction to Discrete Mathematics (A)
    2014   CS/ECE 252: Intro to Computer Engineering (A) 
    CS 520: Intro to Theory of Computing (A)
    Math 431: Intro to Theory of Probability (A)
    End Of Courses Completed in High School
    CS/ECE 352 Digital Systems Fundamentals (A)
    CS 354 Machine Organization and Programming (A)
    CS 564 Intro to Database Managenment Systems (IP)
    CS 368 Learning a New Programming Language (C++) (IP)

***

**Projects**

    Squad - Group Chat Application using Firebase.

***

**Leadsership**

    President - The Hub, UW-Madison’s Computer Science Student Organization.
    Director of Film Production and Industry News - Hollywood Badgers, UW-Madison’s Film and TV Industry          
    Organization    

***   

**Technical Skills**

    Programming: Java, C, Objective-C       Engineering Software: Eclipse, Xcode, Android Studio
    Applications: Word, Pages, Excel, Numbers, Keynote, PowerPoint. Platforms: Android, Java, iOS

***

**Volunteering**

    The Writer’s Institute at UW-Madison (March 2015)
    The Wisconsin Film Festival (April 2014)

***

**Languages** 
   
    English: Native language   Spanish: Basic knowledge  Portuguese: Basic Knowledge

***

**Activities and Interests**

	I enjoy analyzing films, programming, dance music, video games, books, world football and weightlifting.

***

**Acting Experience**

    Lead Actor, Associate Producer: Deadbolt (Hollywood Badgers)
    Lead Actor, The Star (UW-Madison Comm Arts Dep. Student Film)
